---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | RunWhere"
  description="RunWhere is a worked example of the Precomputed AI constraint-baking pattern."
>
  <article class="prose page-shell-narrow">
    <header>
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1 class="page-title">A focused utility for the self-host question.</h1>
    </header>
    <p>
      RunWhere helps practitioners decide whether an open-weight model belongs on their own cloud GPUs or behind a hosted API.
      It is directional by design: the answer is a regime, not a spreadsheet.
    </p>
    <p>
      It is the third worked example in the Precomputed AI trilogy, following RightModel for ruleset compilation and
      CloudEstimate for scheduled generation.
    </p>
    <p>
      The project has no accounts, no billing, and no persistence beyond stable shareable URLs.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
